00:58:01,825 --> 00:58:04,394
So, maybe you're communicating
with a co-worker and it's going

1115
00:58:04,394 --> 00:58:07,431
to say, well, the meeting was
canceled, rescheduled, moved.

1116
00:58:07,431 --> 00:58:09,866
These are kind of formal terms.

1117
00:58:09,866 --> 00:58:11,234
But now, if you're
communicating with someone else,

1118
00:58:11,234 --> 00:58:13,904
we have a different
communication style,

1119
00:58:13,904 --> 00:58:17,541
you might get the meeting was
epic, awesome or a snoozer

1120
00:58:17,541 --> 00:58:20,577
because it learns how you type.

1121
00:58:20,577 --> 00:58:22,245
And, when it does, it does

1122
00:58:22,245 --> 00:58:25,682
so in a way that's always
protecting your privacy.

1123
00:58:25,682 --> 00:58:28,318
All that learning is done
local to the device and none

1124
00:58:28,318 --> 00:58:31,121
of your keystrokes
leave the device.

1125
00:58:31,121 --> 00:58:33,657
Now, QuickType has
great language models

1126
00:58:33,657 --> 00:58:35,525
for all of these languages.

1127
00:58:35,525 --> 00:58:41,865
[ Applause ]

